[2026-03-10T09:10:00Z] [UPDATE] [app.js]
Description: Rewrote FaceScene from contour-tracing particles to a displaced-plane architecture. A uniform grid of ~12,000 particles covers the viewport. When a face is detected via MediaPipe Face Mesh (468 landmarks with x,y,z), each grid particle finds its nearest landmark using a spatial hash. Particles within the influence radius get pulled toward the landmark position with quadratic falloff, and their size/brightness is driven by the landmark's normalised z-depth (nose=bright/large, ears=dim/small). Spring physics with damping animate the transitions. Includes a glow pass for high-depth particles and audio-reactive jitter.
Changes: Replaced FaceScene IIFE entirely — GridParticle class (persistent, no decay), spatial hash (CELL=30px, 3-cell search radius), nearestLandmark(), buildGrid(), updateParticles(), drawParticles(), drawGlowPass(). Fixed TDZ error by using onResizeCallbacks array instead of direct FaceScene reference in resize(). Updated menu card description.
Tests: Browser verified — grid renders as subtle dot plane, Face Mesh model loads (WebGL context created), back button and navigation work. Camera required for full displacement test.
Issues: None
